WEBVTT

00:07.083 --> 00:09.583
-[Gerry sighs]

00:14.500 --> 00:17.166
What are you guys still
doing here? It's 9:20.

00:17.208 --> 00:19.166
I'm twenty minutes late.

00:19.208 --> 00:22.166
Yesterday I was fifteen minutes
late and you didn't leave.

00:22.208 --> 00:25.125
I thought today I'll be twenty
minutes late and maybe
they'll get it.

00:25.166 --> 00:27.291
Maybe they'll be gone when I
come in.

00:27.333 --> 00:29.208
-So, you want us to leave?
-This isn't what I want.

00:29.250 --> 00:31.917
It's what I want for you.
It's what I want you to want.

00:31.959 --> 00:34.083
I want you to want to leave.

00:34.125 --> 00:36.417
Look, when I was a student in
school we had an unwritten rule.

00:36.458 --> 00:38.625
A little student-teacher pact.

00:38.667 --> 00:41.709
If a teacher was fifteen minutes
late, as students, we left.

00:41.750 --> 00:44.750
And we gave that teacher a nice
little break they didn't expect.

00:44.792 --> 00:47.125
It's not something we talked
about, it just happened.

00:47.166 --> 00:50.750
Who sits and stares at
nothing for twenty minutes?

00:50.792 --> 00:52.917
There's nothing on the board.
Who does that?

00:52.959 --> 00:56.625
Not leaders, followers. You kids
today, you don't take
initiative.

00:56.667 --> 00:59.917
Here's what I'm gonna do, I'm
gonna give you a chance to
redeem yourselves tomorrow

00:59.959 --> 01:02.959
and be leaders. I'm going to be
twenty-five minutes late.

01:03.041 --> 01:05.375
[Shh's without a sound]
Write it down, whatever
you gotta do.

01:05.417 --> 01:09.291
When I come in...
I didn't say leave.

01:10.667 --> 01:12.792
-Why would we leave? We're here
to learn.

01:12.834 --> 01:15.000
-Oh, you're here to learn?
'Cause you haven't learned this.

01:15.041 --> 01:17.208
It's been three days.
-We can leave now if you want.

01:17.250 --> 01:19.375
-No, that's not the point.
Then I look like the bad guy.

01:19.417 --> 01:22.625
I thought, maybe I'll come in
late and they'll leave and
they'll do their own thing.

01:22.667 --> 01:24.792
Now you're here.
Congratulations.

01:24.834 --> 01:26.917
[♪ Music]
Open your books.

01:26.959 --> 01:29.083
♪ I'm awesome, no you're
not dude don't lie ♪

01:29.125 --> 01:32.208
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:32.250 --> 01:34.959
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter
of my life gone by ♪

01:39.709 --> 01:42.041
♪ Dance/Workout music

01:42.083 --> 01:44.333
♪ Dance/Workout music

01:44.375 --> 01:46.792
♪ Dance/Workout music

01:47.667 --> 01:50.125
-[DJ]: Great work today
everyone.

01:50.166 --> 01:52.166
See you tomorrow morning.

01:55.375 --> 01:57.959
-[Gerry whispers]: Wow.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.875
Hey. Pretty sweet gig you got.

02:00.917 --> 02:03.000
When did they add a
DJ to the class?

02:03.041 --> 02:05.291
-It was just a trial run for a
few days.

02:05.333 --> 02:09.083
Enrolment hasn't been high,
so this is my last week here.

02:09.125 --> 02:11.000
-[Gerry exhales]

02:11.041 --> 02:13.542
-What if I enrolled in the
class? Would that keep you?

02:13.583 --> 02:15.709
-Probably not.

02:15.750 --> 02:18.583
-Well you sounded great.
So I'm sorry to hear that.

02:18.625 --> 02:21.250
-Thanks. You're sweet.
-Thanks.

02:24.166 --> 02:25.959
Hey, here's a question.

02:26.041 --> 02:28.375
Would you ever consider DJing
a high school dance?

02:28.417 --> 02:32.000
-I'd love to. I've been trying
to break into the high school
market for years.

02:32.041 --> 02:35.041
It's so competitive.
-Soooo competitive.

02:35.083 --> 02:38.291
Well, I happen to teach at
Xavier and we're having a dance.

02:38.333 --> 02:41.125
And the DJ, just like, I got a
text, like, five minutes ago...

02:41.166 --> 02:44.250
that, ah, he can't do it.
-That would be amazing!

02:44.291 --> 02:46.834
When is it?
-It's next Friday...

02:46.875 --> 02:49.041
-Ooh, I can't make it.

02:49.083 --> 02:51.417
-Which is this Friday...
'Cause that's the next Friday.

02:51.458 --> 02:53.917
-That works! Perfect.
-Yeah.

02:53.959 --> 02:56.125
-Thanks so much!
-You're welcome. Thank you!

02:56.166 --> 02:59.041
Six o'clock. Xavier Academy.
See you there...

02:59.083 --> 03:01.250
-Ginger.
-Gerry, with a G.

03:01.291 --> 03:04.917
Ginger with a G.
G+G Music Factory.

03:04.959 --> 03:07.625
-What's that?
-G+G Mus...It's like...

03:07.667 --> 03:09.917
Well, it's C+C Music Factory.
-[Ginger]: Ah.

03:09.959 --> 03:11.917
-And then I just took our
initials.

03:11.959 --> 03:14.333
-Sorry, I've never heard
of them. Bye Gerry!

03:14.375 --> 03:16.208
-Alright. Bye, Ginger.

03:16.250 --> 03:18.458
-[Dave]: Okay, okay, you've
got law of demand.

03:18.500 --> 03:22.792
Where there is an inverse
relationship between price...

03:22.834 --> 03:25.000
And quantity demand.
You feel me?

03:25.041 --> 03:26.875
Then you got law of supply...

03:26.917 --> 03:31.166
Which is the fundamental
principal that states,
if all else is equal,

03:31.208 --> 03:35.792
an increase in price results in
an increase in quantity
supplied.

03:35.834 --> 03:40.041
And that, my budding
learners, is supply and demand.

03:40.083 --> 03:41.208
Any questions?

03:42.834 --> 03:46.083
C'mon, put your phones away.
This is very important stuff.

03:46.125 --> 03:49.291
The whole business world is
driven by supply and demand.

03:49.333 --> 03:51.458
Anyone?

03:51.500 --> 03:54.000
Yes! Brandon, my man!

03:54.041 --> 03:57.875
-Um, Mr. Bechara, is this all
gonna be on the next test?

03:57.917 --> 03:59.834
-Yeah! Of course.
Why wouldn't it be?

03:59.875 --> 04:02.917
-Well, do you think you can
repeat the whole second half?

04:02.959 --> 04:07.750
'Cause I wasn't listening to,
I don't think a word of anything
that you just said.

04:07.792 --> 04:10.875
I zoned out.
-Anyone else zone out?

04:13.166 --> 04:15.625
[♪ Music]
-Mr. Dwyer!

04:15.667 --> 04:17.875
I caught these girls smoking
in the library.

04:17.917 --> 04:20.333
This is the third time.
Something has to be done.

04:20.375 --> 04:23.542
-You know smoking's bad for you?
-Give me a break, it's not the
end of the world.

04:23.583 --> 04:27.417
-As a matter of fact, it's the
end of many people's worlds.

04:27.458 --> 04:31.333
I can find you some literature
if you care to read up on it.

04:31.375 --> 04:33.291
-Reading's for losers.
-[Emma gasps]

04:33.333 --> 04:36.166
-Mr. Dwyer, isn't there
something you want to say?

04:36.208 --> 04:38.291
-Ladies, listen.

04:40.792 --> 04:43.000
Stop smoking. Don't do it again.

04:43.959 --> 04:46.041
Get goin' to class.

04:47.166 --> 04:49.041
-[Emma]: What...?

04:49.083 --> 04:51.458
I heard you were soft,
but that was ridiculous.

04:51.500 --> 04:53.542
-[Dwyer]: Look, kids will be
kids.

04:53.583 --> 04:56.792
-Those spoiled brats need to be
taught a lesson before they burn
down the whole school!

04:56.834 --> 04:59.917
-Ah c'mon, it's cool.
-You are the Vice Principal!

04:59.959 --> 05:02.208
Maybe you should start
acting like one!

05:03.834 --> 05:05.875
-Life's still good.

05:05.917 --> 05:08.917
-It's a dance, don't miss the
dance. Boys, be there at the
dance.

05:08.959 --> 05:12.375
Guys, dance Friday. Do not
forget to show up.

05:12.417 --> 05:14.542
Stephan, dance Friday.
Thank you.

05:14.583 --> 05:16.709
-I didn't know there was a
dance this week.

05:16.750 --> 05:18.875
-Yeah, that's 'cause I just
organized it.

05:18.917 --> 05:20.792
-If you need a DJ, my
cousin can do it.
-Read the flyer.

05:20.834 --> 05:22.959
I have a DJ who's way better
than your cousin.

05:23.000 --> 05:25.375
-You don't know my cousin.
-No, I don't want to know your
cousin.

05:25.417 --> 05:28.000
Just spread the word. Here, take
some of these and pass them out.

05:28.041 --> 05:29.917
Thank you!

05:29.959 --> 05:32.291
And there's no fun fair,
there's a dance.

05:32.333 --> 05:35.375
Let's get that up there.
-[Malik]: I never hear this.

05:35.417 --> 05:37.583
I have recently taken
Two-Step classes.

05:37.625 --> 05:40.917
Perhaps Malik will attend dance?

05:40.959 --> 05:44.083
-Yes you will attend the dance,
because...

05:44.125 --> 05:46.917
Who's gonna clean up...before?

05:46.959 --> 05:49.083
And who's gonna clean up after?
-Malik.

05:49.125 --> 05:51.291
-Yeah.
-Always Malik.

05:51.333 --> 05:53.542
-Ahhh da da da, da.
Timmy. Timmy.

05:53.583 --> 05:55.709
I was literally just coming
over here...

05:55.750 --> 05:58.542
to put a poster up for the
dance...Right here.

05:58.583 --> 06:01.417
-[Out of breath]: I'm really
hoping, to get this bone marrow
transplant.

06:01.458 --> 06:04.166
-[Interrupts]: I'm hoping to
have a dance. I'm not even
listening to you.

06:04.208 --> 06:06.375
-You can't just run around the
school throwin' posters up.

06:06.417 --> 06:09.208
You have to have permission.
I have permission. Hold
these, help me out.

06:09.250 --> 06:12.208
This is the dance the school
has been waiting for.

06:12.250 --> 06:14.750
All the information, okay?
Are you coming?

06:14.792 --> 06:16.709
-My doctor's not gonna
like that.

06:16.750 --> 06:19.166
-Don't ask your doctor, just
come. You sweat your ass off.

06:19.208 --> 06:22.333
Get some energy going.
It's awesome, alright?

06:22.375 --> 06:24.750
Okay? I want you there.

06:24.792 --> 06:26.834
I'm watching for you.
give me those flyers.

06:26.875 --> 06:29.000
And get goin'.
-[Timmy]: Sorry sir.

06:29.041 --> 06:31.709
-[Gerry]: You're right,
don't say sorry.

06:31.750 --> 06:33.917
-I don't understand these kids.
I mean, I love teaching.

06:33.959 --> 06:37.583
And I love what I teach. I put
my heart and soul into each
lesson.

06:37.625 --> 06:39.667
But I'm faced with a sea of
dead eyes.

06:39.709 --> 06:43.125
-And that bothers you because...
-'Cause I'm only reaching 20% of
my class.

06:43.166 --> 06:45.792
-Perfect. You're a hundred
percent on track.
-What?

06:45.834 --> 06:48.792
-Look, you can never
reach all of the kids.

06:48.834 --> 06:51.792
Kids fall through the cracks and
that's just teaching.

06:51.834 --> 06:54.834
-That's not how I teach.
I wanna reach them all.

06:54.875 --> 06:57.208
-[Laughs]: That's adorable.

06:57.250 --> 07:00.959
Listen, if there's one tactic
that I've observed over the
years

07:01.000 --> 07:05.125
that can really keep a teacher
afloat, it's this: care less.

07:05.166 --> 07:08.875
-Aren't you the guidance
counsellor? That's really bleak.

07:08.917 --> 07:12.083
-Yeah, you wanted to see me?
-Are you planning a...

07:12.125 --> 07:14.709
"Dace" Friday?
-It's supposed to say dance.

07:14.750 --> 07:17.500
Charlie did that one,
he's not a good speller.

07:17.542 --> 07:20.750
-Isn't he?
It's cancelled.

07:20.792 --> 07:22.709
I banned dances.
-You banned them? When?

07:22.750 --> 07:25.208
-When I took over as principal.
-Ugh.

07:25.250 --> 07:27.917
-Tasty treats, sultry beats
too tempting a mix, Gerry.

07:27.959 --> 07:30.208
-Okay Robert, that is
ridiculous.

07:30.250 --> 07:32.542
-You know what's ridiculous,
Gerry? Teen births.

07:32.583 --> 07:36.125
You know when they occur?
Nine months after teen dances.
No dice.

07:36.166 --> 07:38.792
-You just made that up.
-You know what you're gonna
have to make up?

07:38.834 --> 07:41.458
A thousand new flyers announcing
that your dance is cancelled.

07:41.500 --> 07:44.792
Or dace, up to you. But you're
not gonna do it on school hours.

07:44.834 --> 07:47.333
-Okay, fine but that's
gonna take a long time.

07:47.375 --> 07:50.083
Well past Friday, so why don't
we just let this dance go?

07:50.125 --> 07:52.959
