desensitized.

12:17.458 --> 12:19.709
[Girls laugh]
-Yeah.

12:19.750 --> 12:22.834
-[All chant]: We want to dance!
We want to dance!

12:22.875 --> 12:26.458
We want to dance!
We want to dance!

12:26.500 --> 12:30.291
We want to dance!
We want to dance!

12:30.333 --> 12:33.166
-What is going on here?
-[Gerry]: Principal Cheeley.

12:33.208 --> 12:36.500
It's our right to dance and if
you take that away from us,
we have nothing.

12:36.542 --> 12:41.083
Without dance how is Stephan,
here, gonna learn to deal
with rejection?

12:41.125 --> 12:43.959
-Wait...
-Or how will Lucy learn to
loosen up?

12:44.000 --> 12:46.417
And stop being so boring
all the time.

12:46.458 --> 12:48.583
Dances have been the
foundation of human connection

12:48.625 --> 12:51.208
since the very first school
opened in 1975.

12:51.250 --> 12:54.125
They've always been a place for
students to connect with one
another.

12:54.166 --> 12:58.208
For people to fall in love and
teachers and DJ's become one.

12:58.250 --> 13:00.333
-[Mouths]: Wha...?
-[Gerry]: Anything can happen.

13:00.375 --> 13:05.333
So we are here to ask you
to change your mind so we
can dance.

13:05.375 --> 13:07.291
Do it for the Stephans.

13:07.333 --> 13:09.667
Or the Lucys.

13:10.333 --> 13:12.709
Or the...Do...??

13:15.875 --> 13:18.125
[Whispers]: Who is that guy,
in the yellow shirt?

13:18.166 --> 13:21.417
-We thought he was with you.
-Why would he be with me?

13:21.458 --> 13:24.333
What do you think I bring
teenagers to my work
to hang out all day?

13:24.375 --> 13:26.417
-I think he goes to my cousin's
school

13:26.458 --> 13:29.500
-Hey! Who are you?
-I just want to dance.

13:29.542 --> 13:32.333
-Who here would ever dance...
-Mr. Duncan! Stay with the tour.

13:32.375 --> 13:36.792
Though I enjoyed the show
immensely, the answer's
still no.

13:36.834 --> 13:41.125
And I don't want to
hear another word
about the dance!

13:46.625 --> 13:49.125
-Okay everybody!
It is learn time.

13:49.166 --> 13:51.291
Who wants a phone?
-Whoa, that's my phone.

13:51.333 --> 13:54.959
-I'm selling them for sixty
bucks after school.
Who wants one?

13:55.000 --> 13:57.917
Okay good. Okay good.
Okay good!

13:57.959 --> 14:00.166
Looks like I'm gonna make
some serious money here.

14:00.208 --> 14:03.417
But wait! Some guy named
Nick, just opened a store

14:03.458 --> 14:07.667
across the street selling the
same phone for $55 dollars!

14:09.291 --> 14:13.458
[Italian accent]: Heeey
everybody, it's Italian Nick!

14:13.500 --> 14:15.417
Why buy from Mr. Bechara?

14:15.458 --> 14:18.792
